# Skye Standard

## What This File Is

This file defines Skye Standard from the truth of the whole project, not from the narrow view of the Theia launcher layer.

The earlier mistake was treating the standard as if it were mostly about SkyeCDE, Theia, launcher plumbing, and IDEia shell parity.

That is not your actual stack.

Your actual stack is a wider operating ecosystem made of multiple platform families, multiple runtimes, multiple control planes, multiple storage systems, real mail lanes, real serverless backends, real edge workers, real release and audit surfaces, and sovereign primitives that are already partially modeled inside the repo.

So Skye Standard must be defined from that fuller reality.

